"I will vote for you, mainly because you deal with ecoogy" — thank you! —

00:26:50.200 --> 00:26:54.000
"and I'd like to know how you intend to phase out nuclear power?"

00:26:54.000 --> 00:26:55.080
Well, it's simple!

00:26:55.860 --> 00:26:57.860
In a way, all we need to do is take the decision!

00:26:58.080 --> 00:27:01.720
And we have to do it quick, because we lost a lot of time.

00:27:02.180 --> 00:27:04.900
And of course, the more we linger, the more it will take time to do it,

00:27:04.900 --> 00:27:07.820
because there are two aspects to phasing out nuclear power.

00:27:07.900 --> 00:27:10.820
There's the stopping of nuclear production of electricity on the one hand,

00:27:11.160 --> 00:27:16.260
and this immediately raises a problem, because we have to replace it with renewable energies.

00:27:16.520 --> 00:27:18.520
100 % renewable energies must be our objective,

00:27:18.520 --> 00:27:21.940
but you have to understand that we will do it progressively.

00:27:21.940 --> 00:27:25.260
I'm not going to tell you: "Listen, we're going to stop all the nuclear power plants in the country tomorrow,"

00:27:25.420 --> 00:27:26.480
"and then we'll see".

00:27:26.480 --> 00:27:27.660
We couldn't do that!

00:27:27.800 --> 00:27:30.500
It could cause the collapse of the electricity network.

00:27:31.060 --> 00:27:40.320
When we close a nuclear power plant, we have to have the steady equivalent of energy production.

00:27:40.500 --> 00:27:42.360
So it's all about planning.

00:27:42.360 --> 00:27:48.940
Planning means organizing and connecting decisions and the means to carry them out.

00:27:49.040 --> 00:27:51.040
That's the way we'll do it.

00:27:51.120 --> 00:27:54.720
Once we stopped a nuclear power plant,

00:27:54.980 --> 00:28:01.380
— which means that we've replaced it with renewable energies — then we have to dismantle it,

00:28:01.380 --> 00:28:09.080
and let me tell you that it is one more reason to massively fund nuclear research.

00:28:09.220 --> 00:28:12.240
Why? Because we need to cool nuclear waste.

00:28:12.360 --> 00:28:22.160
We'll have to wait several thousand years before nuclear waste's radioactivity decays.

00:28:22.700 --> 00:28:28.700
The only way we can cool nuclear waste is to fund nuclear research, it won't cool on its own.

00:28:29.960 --> 00:28:31.340
So it'll take time.

00:28:32.300 --> 00:28:34.140
It'll take time, and that's precisely the problem.

00:28:34.140 --> 00:28:39.060
As to dismantling a nuclear power plant, it is a very complicated operation.

00:28:39.360 --> 00:28:43.940
Everything that is dismantled has to be transformed into waste,

00:28:44.200 --> 00:28:49.920
and this waste has to be as harmless as possible, although completely harmless waste doesn't exist.

00:28:50.700 --> 00:28:53.360
So that's the way we'll proceed,
and that's not the easiest part.

00:28:53.440 --> 00:28:56.200
And contrary to what some simpletons say,

00:28:56.560 --> 00:28:59.860
phasing out nuclear energy doesn't mean we'll have to use candles again.

00:28:59.860 --> 00:29:04.400
On the contrary, we'll have to make huge technological leaps to replace it,

00:29:04.440 --> 00:29:09.280
but let me reassure you, we know how to do this, we can replace it with renewable energies.

00:29:09.320 --> 00:29:12.800
Our problem is neither finding renewable energies,

00:29:12.900 --> 00:29:18.840
nor how to make them work effeciciently enough according to our needs.

00:29:19.080 --> 00:29:21.260
Our only problem is to organize the phasing out of nuclear energy.

00:29:21.760 --> 00:29:23.640
Renewable energies already are available.

00:29:23.820 --> 00:29:30.960
For instance, the motion of the sea contains 75 times the energy that our planet needs

00:29:30.960 --> 00:29:34.860
to keep our civilization of waste going.

00:29:34.980 --> 00:29:36.400
As you can see, it's not so complicated.

00:29:36.560 --> 00:29:39.840
Our problem is not to find the means.
Our problem is to carry them out.

00:29:40.300 --> 00:29:42.300
So we can do this, and we will.

